to place the Jewish community in its proper perspective in Canadian life and the non-Jewish community in its proper perspective with respect to Jewish life in one part of Canada. These essays, therefore, include some that are frankly historical in nature, some which deal with contemporary issues in historical perspective, some which reveal the essence of Jewish existence, and some which deal with the faith of Reform Judaism and its probable direction in the second half of the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aJewszCanadaxHistory. 0aReform JudaismzCanada. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / Theology.2bisacsh1 aCraig, Gerald M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEnoch Kagan, Henry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFackenheim, Emil L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeinberg, Abraham L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIsserman, Ferdinand M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKamerling, Aaron M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKayfetz, Ben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRose, Albert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRose, Albert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchipper, Sidney S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeeley, John R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilberman, Lou H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeinstein, Jacob J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWrong, Dennis H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is p